<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Lunch Roulette</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, user-scalable=yes">

    <link rel='stylesheet prefetch' href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans'>
    <link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/menu.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/home.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/containers.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- dropdown menu -->
    <div class="dropdown">
      <button class="dropbtn">Menu</button>
      <div class="dropdown-content">
        <a href="/home">Home</a>
        <a href="/my_lunches">Past Lunches</a>
        <a href="/my_profile">My Profile</a>
        <a href="/current_room">The Lunch Room</a>
        <a href="/logout">Log Out</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- end dropdown menu -->
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Help!</h2>

      <div class="help-row">
          <h3>Getting started!</h3>
          
          <div class="help-div">
              Welcome to The Lunch People! 
              Ever wish you could get to know people from other departments? 
              The Lunch People aims to improve co-workers/colleagues relation through lunch meetings!
          </div>
          
          <div class="help-div">
              To get started, you can start by pressing the roll button from the 
              home screen. Once that is done, you will be matched up with 3 other co-workers. You and 
              your 3 other colleagues will be put into a lunch room and in the mean time, you can click
              to view their profile so you have some idea where this person is coming from. 
          </div>
          
          <div class="help-div">
              In your free time, you can go ahead and edit your profile so other people can get to know 
              you easier! The more the better!
          </div>
          
          <div class="help-div"> 
              you can also head to your past lunches incase you enjoyed your last lunch and wanted to 
              stay in contact with the people you had lunch with. 
          </div>
          
          <h3> Coming soon! </h3>
          
          <div class="help-div"> 
              You will be able to take someone to lunch with you incase you are feeling the need for a 
              wingman! woot woot! Stay tuned!
          </div>
          
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- scripts -->
    <script src='http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.3/jquery.min.js'></script>
    <script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
  </body>
